Project 8 | Build a Chatbot for L'Oréal
L’Oréal is exploring the power of AI, and your job is to showcase what's possible. Your task is to build a chatbot that helps users discover and understand L’Oréal’s extensive range of products—makeup, skincare, haircare, and fragrances—as well as provide personalized routines and recommendations.

Project Steps Overview:
Click this starter file link to launch your own Codespace. Your starter code includes:
●	HTML for a chat interface with header, footer, chat area, input field, and send button. 
●	A L’Oréal logo image to use for branding your chatbot.
●	Basic CSS styles to structure the layout.
●	JavaScript (script.js) handling basic user interaction: capturing input and displaying it in the chat window.
●	Cloudflare Worker helper script (RESOURCE_cloudflare-worker.js) pre-configured for secure API communication.
Add Branding & Customize Appearance
●	Add the provided L’Oréal logo to your page.
●	Update your CSS styles to use L’Oréal branded colors. Ensure the visual design aligns with L’Oréal’s brand identity.
●	Review a case study of L’Oréal fonts from Monotype, a global company specializing in type design and font licensing.
Obtain Your API Key
●	Get your OpenAI API key from the OpenAI dashboard. Temporarily store your key in a local file called secrets.js within your Codespace.
Configure the Chatbot
●	Write a clear, concise system prompt for your chatbot that guides it to only answer questions related to L’Oréal products, routines, and recommendations. 
●	Modify the JavaScript (script.js) to:
○	Capture user input from the chat interface.
○	Send requests to OpenAI's Chat Completions API.
○	Display chatbot responses clearly within the chat interface.
Ensure AI Relevance
●	Configure your AI to politely refuse to answer questions unrelated to L’Oréal products, routines, recommendations, beauty-related topics, etc.
Create a Cloudflare Worker & Secure Your API Key
●	Create a Cloudflare Worker for your project.
●	Securely store your API key in Cloudflare under "Variables and Secrets."
●	Deploy your Cloudflare Worker using the provided helper script (RESOURCE_cloudflare-worker.js).
●	Watch the video "Protecting Your API Key with Cloudflare" in the 🍿AI Privacy and Safety Skillbuilder if you need a refresher on deploying securely.
●	Note the Cloudflare Worker URL provided after deployment.
Update Your Chatbot to Use Cloudflare Worker Endpoint
●	Update your JavaScript (script.js) to send requests to your deployed Cloudflare Worker endpoint URL instead of directly to OpenAI.
●	Verify that your chatbot correctly communicates through your Cloudflare Worker.
Ready for a LevelUp? (25 pts extra credit)
●	Maintain Conversation History (10 pts): Enable your chatbot to track the context of the conversation, including details like the user's name and past questions, to support natural, multi-turn interactions. 
●	Display User Question (5 pts): Display the user's latest question just above the chat response, like in the project preview image. It resets with each new question.
●	Chat Conversation UI (10 pts): Design your chatbot interface to mimic a real conversation, using distinct message bubbles for user and assistant messages. This layout enhances readability and provides a familiar chat experience.
Test & Submit
●	Use DevTools to check functionality and responsiveness across different screen sizes.
●	Commit and push your changes to GitHub.
●	Deploy your site and submit the live link. Ensure your link works correctly by testing in an incognito or private browser.


